taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus aberrans sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet ‘’ refers to abnormal wing venation: this species has three submarginal cells instead of two (Fig.2).

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus alatus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to wing shaped lateral lobes of the male S7.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus albipilosus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to short white pubescence on the scutum.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus albiscopis sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to the white scopa pubescence on the hind tibia of the female.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus aliceafontanus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to the distribution of this species around Alice Springs.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus altispinosus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to the robust setae on the tip of the ventral apical lobe of male sterna 7. It also is a translation of the name of our linguistic advisor Wiebe Hogendoorn.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus aratus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to very coarse pit-reticulate sculpture on the head.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus auricorneus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to the orange coloured antennae.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus bidentatus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to the two teeth on the ventral margin of the clypeus.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus ciliatus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to the ciliate inner hind tibial spur.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus claviger sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to the club-shaped apical lobe of the male seventh sterna.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus consobrinus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to the average

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus constrictus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to strongly depressed post gradular areas ofT2–3 in both sexes.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus laciniosus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to fringe of white hairs on the posteriorT2–4.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus longivultu sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to the elongated face of this species.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus lucidus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to the smooth and shiny integument on head, scutum and terga of this species.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus nitidifuscus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to very smooth and brown integument of large parts of the body of this species.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus pectinatus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to the strongly pectinate inner hind tibial spur.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus pilotapilus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to the dense and short pubescence on the scutum.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus quadripinnatus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to thin feathery like apical lobes of the male sterna 7.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus rubicundus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to the colour of the female metasoma.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus rubricinctus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to the red colouration of the anterior parts of theT2–4.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus similis sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to the common habitus of this species within this subgenus.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus splendens sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to the smooth and shiny integument on metapostnotum and terga of this species.

taxonomicNameUsageLabel: Leioproctus submetallicus sec Leijs, Dorey, Hogendoorn 2018
etymology: The specific epithet refers to the faint metallic shine on the head and thorax.
